g
le to go to Veryan. I know we got down to King Harry Ferry and - they'd just finished their last trip across 'til dinnertime. But he tipped the ferrymen and they took us across and - I know we - we came back the same night and Veryan quite a long way for 
a
 pony and jingle. But when we got back to Tuckingmill the toll gates were there then, and they were closed, and they open - they had to open the toll gate, they had to wake up the man, he was gone to bed, to come out and open the gate. I think you had to 
pay a penny to go through. I remember that as a tiny boy I woke up then.
