ys but I never came in contact much with them. But I remember - Mrs Bassett - bought a pony from my father. My father used to go to Summercourt every year and bring home a young pony and train it. And he had two little black ponies. And - one of their - M
r
s Basset's ponies, they had a pair of ponies, one of 'em died, one of these ponies, and they took a fancy to a - one of me father's, and - the butler, he was sent over to my father's place to ask if he would sell this pony. He sold this pony to Mrs Basset
 to - to match the one she had, I remember that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid8480765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11556911\charrsid8926906 He went to the horse fair at Summercourt?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid675531 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11556911\charrsid8926906 Summercourt, every year they used to have a fair there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid8480765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11556911\charrsid8926906 Would he often bring home ponies to sell?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid675531 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11556911\charrsid8926906 Well my father always - brought home a pony. 
Then he would eventually sell this pony to somebody after he'd trained it you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid8480765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11556911\charrsid8926906 That was the Bassets of Tehidy, the great landowners?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid675531 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11556911\charrsid8926906 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid8480765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11556911\charrsid8926906 
Do you remember anyone showing respect to your parents in these sort of ways, referring to them as sir or madam?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid675531 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11556911\charrsid8926906 No, I don't think so.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid8480765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11556911\charrsid8926906 It wasn't generally done?
