Can you remember being brought up to treat people of one sort differently from people of another?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid675531 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11556911\charrsid8926906 No, I don't myself, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid8480765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11556911\charrsid8926906 In the town of {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}
{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname City}}Camborne{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose} where you lived who were considered generally to be the most important people?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid675531 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11556911\charrsid8926906 
Most important? Well - we had a few - squires they used to call 'em them days, and then - we never seen much of them, not when I - I was a boy.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid8480765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11556911\charrsid8926906 In the town itself was anybody thought to be of special importance?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid675531 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11556911\charrsid8926906 Well - I don't know anybody particular.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid8480765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11556911\charrsid8926906 The clergy, would they have been sort of special?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid675531 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11556911\charrsid8926906 
Well they - they didn't visit very much them days, not - the clergy. Pretty much the same today I believe, don't seem to bother much so long as they - get their collection.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid8480765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11556911\charrsid8926906 What about schoolteachers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid675531 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11556911\charrsid8926906 Schoolteachers - one I remember mostly is Mr Quintrell, at the 
{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname address}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname Street}}Basset Road{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose} school. Very fine teacher, nice fellow.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid8480765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11556911\charrsid8926906 He would have been respected?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid675531 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11556911\charrsid8926906 O
h yes. Yes. The schoolmaster was called Davies. I don't think he liked me very much, because - I suppose in politics I was opposite side to him 'cos I remember I very often get a bit late and get the cane coming in. Well I came in with two of his - friend
s one day and I got off scott free. Didn't like to - cane me and - and lave the others go, so I got off that day. I remember that.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid8480765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11556911\charrsid8926906 These friends would be other pupils?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid675531 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11556911\charrsid8926906 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid8480765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11556911\charrsid8926906 Some personal friends of Mr Davies?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid675531 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11556911\charrsid8926906 Yes, they were in - in a 
- business people in the town I suppose more business - more - up in class I suppose than myself or my father.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid8480765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11556911\charrsid8926906 They would have been thought to have been important in the town?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid675531 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11556911\charrsid8926906 Yes, important, that's right. I remember as a tiny boy we had these h
ere - combustion stoves in the centre of the - of the classroom, for heating the school. And I remember we had to gather right around this here for warmth you see. And I remember being accused of pushing one of the - one little kiddie in on the - on this 
here stove, I never done it, but that always played on my mind. I was - I had the fault for somebody else.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid8480765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11556911\charrsid8926906 No guards around the stoves those days?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid675531 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11556911\charrsid8926906 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid8480765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11556911\charrsid8926906 What about farmers, would they have been or any special importance?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid675531 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11556911\charrsid8926906 Farmers? No, I d
on't think so. Of course they had a lot of property then, lot of fields then. Sir Eva, he was the biggest farmer around our area.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid8480765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11556911\charrsid8926906 He would be in town on market day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid675531 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11556911\charrsid8926906 
Yes. Oh yes. Of course he had - they had a big market in them days - in Camborne.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid8480765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11556911\charrsid8926906 Who were the main employers in the town?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid675531 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11556911\charrsid8926906 
Main employers. Well - I can't remember exactly. Mills I think was one, down at {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname address}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname Street}}Trealawney Road{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}
, he was the principal builder in them days. I think it was his son that was - that came in with me when I - got scott free from the caning, one of his sons I think. He was a principal builder in them days. Wasn't so many big builders in them days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid8480765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11556911\charrsid8926906 Who would have been the principle employer or labour in the town then?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid675531 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11556911\charrsid8926906 Well - that would be mining the
m days. I don't remember much about Holman's, 'cos Holman's, they - started as silversmiths so I've been told. And - I had a - oven - a oven door here given me one day, Holman Brothers, Camborne, so I asked my brother if he would like that for the - museu
m they've got at Camborne. He said, no, we don't want that. Of course perhaps he didn't like the idea of Holman's Brothers' as stove smiths. But that was original start.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid8480765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11556911\charrsid8926906 They would have been the biggest employers in the town?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid675531 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11556911\charrsid8926906 Yes, oh yes, yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid8480765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11556911\charrsid8926906 Holmans as people, did they live in the town?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid675531 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11556911\charrsid8926906 
Oh yes. They - they were very - very good as regards sport. They used to - encourage the - the football team, 'cos I remember - my brother saying that - he met a fellow from South Africa, came hom
e, said, what's the matter with the football team, no football team here now. So, he said, no, he said, we - run out of funds. Well, he said, well go up and see Mr - Thomas and Mr Holman and see if we can get some money to start the team again. Well they 
w
ent up to Mr Fred Tomas' and he was in playing billiards with Mr Holman, they had billiard tables them days upstairs and - he - gave 'em, I think it was ten pound to start off the team again, that started the Camborne team up - after - some years being wi
thout a club.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid8480765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11556911\charrsid8926906 
Who would the Homan's consider to be their equals, to be their social equals, who would they mix with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid675531 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11556911\charrsid8926906 
Well the Thomas' you see, they were mining people. And - them and - and Holmans were the principle - employers them days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid8480765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11556911\charrsid8926906 Who would teachers mix with and associate with as their friends and equals?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid675531 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11556911\charrsid8926906 
Well I don't know that they done much out in public. - Of course they had all their - facilities at home I suppose, billiard tables and things like that. Of course they were gr
eat people at the Wesleyan chapel there. But I don't if they done any active - work in the town.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid8480765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11556911\charrsid8926906 Socially would they mix with the clergy as friends would you think?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid675531 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11556911\charrsid8926906 Not that I know of. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid8480765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11556911\charrsid8926906 Could you think who the clergy would associate with
 as friends and equals, apart from their Ministry?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid675531 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11556911\charrsid8926906 No, I don't remember that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid8480765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11556911\charrsid8926906 Do you remember any of them, except the Reverend Shimmin, as people?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid675531 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11556911\charrsid8926906 
No. Because - the first - the vicar that I remember in Camborne was Reverend Hooper. Becaus
e he married us. He - he wasn't much of a preacher I didn't think but he was - he had plenty of money, his wife had a lot of money. Done a lot of good in the town. And - I've been told whether it's a person down - down near the recreation ground - in very
 
poor circumstances, and Mr Roland the coalman came in with - five hundredweight of coal. She said, I can't pay that Mr Roland. He said, don't matter about that, he said, doesn't matter who's paying, there's the coal. And - anonymous Mr Hopper - the vicar 
- through the - the doctor at the time would say who was in bad circumstances and - he would - pass over - send this coal round to people anonymously.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid8480765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11556911\charrsid8926906 He was the vicar of Camborne?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid675531 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11556911\charrsid8926906 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid8480765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11556911\charrsid8926906 Mr Davies the schoolmaster, he was a local preacher as well wasn't he?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid675531 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11556911\charrsid8926906 Yes, that's right, yes. At Wesleyan. I think he was a good master.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid8480765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11556911\charrsid8926906 What sort of people would you say went to church?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid675531 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11556911\charrsid8926906 
You want to know who went to church - mostly. Well I think the - the monied people, they went to - the Chu
rch of England, and of course the Wesleyan chapel, that was - a very principle place for - monied people, but the Centenary chapel, that was mostly - attended by the Holman brothers, they were great non-conformists. But - I think a lot of people went to c
h
urch in them days, business people, to advertise their business. I remember there was a - a singer here in the Centenary chapel in the choir, he had a very loud voice. And he was that loud he could drown the choir and they had to turn him out - the choir.
 Well he got a sitting then, 'cos in them days, they used to pay to have their own - seats in the chapels and churches, and this singer - got a sitting up in the - side gallery near the chapel, and he sang louder than ever.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid8480765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11556911\charrsid8926906 You can't remember anybody else particularly who went to church?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid675531 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11556911\charrsid8926906 
No, I think the doctors - attended the - the church at Camborne. And the - I know one doctor, he was greatly in touch with the - with the vicar there, one doctor was, and they used to make anonymous gifts to poor 
people. And - I remember - a person living down near the recreation ground had five hundredweight of coal took in to her. The Pendarves family used to attend the church at Treslothan. Is a little walk from the estate - leading to the church. They had thei
r own - seat there. And I remember the boys - Church Lads Brigade going down to Pendarves, we were entertained by - Mrs Pendarves, and I remember as a boy going on the lake there with a boat. We had a lovely supper, I remember that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid8480765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11556911\charrsid8926906 You mentioned the c
oncerts in Camborne, can you recall who that singer was now?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid675531 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11556911\charrsid8926906 
Oh that was Fanny Moody. I remember as a boy - being on the outside of the Public Rooms, I think the Public Rooms packed with people, and crowds were outside, to hear Fanny Moody. And I be
lieve my mother said that she went to school with Fanny Moody, at Bond Street, Redruth, little dwelling house that held a school there. Sort of private school. And I think that - her father was called Moody. I think they kept the photographers shop there 
at {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname address}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname Street}}Bond Street{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}. I remember going to Lanner with my mother as a tiny boy to visit my father's sister, Aunt Mary Anne Morcombe, she lived at 
{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname address}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname Street}}Church Road{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}, Lanner. She kept a penny school, but she couldn't read or write. I suppose it was done to - people to sen
d their children out the way. Anyhow, her husband, Tom Morcombe, he had a big shovel with a hole in it, I remember as a tiny boy going up to see him - circling around this here tin stone, he used to grind the tin out with this here - big shovel, and he to
ld me that - the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13585395\charrsid8926906 Re}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11556911\charrsid8926906 
esavane people opened the mine the wrong place, he said, the tin is up here by Penstruthal where I get my tinstone from. And - if they went up there I shouldn't get my tinstone. I remember she had a big spy glass they called it, oh very p
owerful, in the front room and - she said, when I die, Telfer, you shall have that there spy glass, but I never got him. Don't know where he's still now. Using - using it but - it was kept in the front room towards the window, you could look out and see a
ll over Lanner with this here spy glass. I remember - having a good look at it, it was very powerful it was.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid8480765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11556911\charrsid8926906 
Where you lived did all the people in the working or lower class have the same standard of living, or would you say there were different groups?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid675531 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11556911\charrsid8926906 
Well I - I don't think that - there were a lot of difference, of course if - the poor people, they had a more simpler diet I suppose, but we always lived very well. My mother, she was a very good cook and used to cook a lot. Used to have a lot of s
avoury meals and so on. She also used to bake her own bread and cake.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid8480765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11556911\charrsid8926906 
Do you think that one group within the working population felt itself superior in any way to the rest?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid675531 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11556911\charrsid8926906 Well I don't know that - I don't think much superiority.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid8480765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11556911\charrsid8926906 Were some families thought of as rough and others respectable?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid675531 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11556911\charrsid8926906 
Yes, of course - I don't think there's any - roughness amongst children them days like there is today. They seemed to be more friendly, I don't think you had the rivalry that they've got today. They seemed to be more - amiable people.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid8480765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11556911\charrsid8926906 Neighbourly?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid675531 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11556911\charrsid8926906 Yes. Oh yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid8480765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11556911\charrsid8926906 
Do you remember if there was any distinction of this kind between craftsmen or tradesmen and labourers?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid675531 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11556911\charrsid8926906 No, I don't think there's any rivalry that way. Of course - 
when you went to learn your - your trade you had a very low wage and of course the - the - the labourers they could get bigger money right away.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid8480765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11556911\charrsid8926906 But eventually?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid675531 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11556911\charrsid8926906 
Yes, I - I think - a labourer in them days, he could get - sixteen, eighteen shilling a week, but a - a craftsman he would get perhaps over a pound, twenty-one or - some may get as much as twenty-four shilling a week.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid8480765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11556911\charrsid8926906 
Did mother and father have the same attitude to people in different classes and groups?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid675531 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11556911\charrsid8926906 Yes, I - I think so, I think the - my parents respected everybody.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid8480765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11556911\charrsid8926906 
Did you think mother saw herself as belonging to a particular social class or group?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid675531 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11556911\charrsid8926906 No I don't think so.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid8480765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11556911\charrsid8926906 Was it possible at that time to move from one class or group to another?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid675531 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11556911\charrsid8926906 No I don't think there was any - any moves that way.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid8480765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11556911\charrsid8926906 
You can't remember anyone who sort of made good or became better off or worse off?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid675531 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11556911\charrsid8926906 No, I don't think there was any opportunity that way.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid8480765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11556911\charrsid8926906 Do you remember anyone being described as a real gentleman or a real lady?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid675531 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11556911\charrsid8926906 No, I don't remember that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid8480765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11556911\charrsid8926906 Do you remember seeing a policeman around where you lived as a child?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid675531 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11556911\charrsid8926906 
Oh yes - the policeman them days, their - their big job was to stop boys and - these here little games they play at night times.
 Yes, I remember - being chased many times when I was been - putting sort of things - annoying neighbours or - tic-tac we used to call it, tapping the windows and tying the doors and - putting the bag over chimneys and - 'course the policemen them days, t
hey - they were kept busy protecting the neighbours and these here boys, 'cos we had no cinemas, nowhere else to go, we had to make our own fun.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid8480765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11556911\charrsid8926906 When you were naughty did your mother every say, I'll call a policeman?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid675531 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11556911\charrsid8926906 She may have done. But I reme
mber we were out in the - in the road throwing stones or something, and the policeman - happened to see us and see us run in and we ran underneath the table. But he just shouted and - said he - what he - what he would do and that was all. They were all fr
iendly in them days I think, policemen were.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid8480765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11556911\charrsid8926906 How do you think he treated the people?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid675531 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11556911\charrsid8926906 
How they treated us people. Well they were very friendly I think, they - I don't think they were out - out of place in that way.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid8480765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11556911\charrsid8926906 Your parents had your home on a mortgage did they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid675531 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11556911\charrsid8926906 Mortgage?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid8480765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11556911\charrsid8926906 It wasn't rented, had they bought it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid675531 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11556911\charrsid8926906 
What, the property? Oh - oh that was on the life system to start with. But we eventually got a - a lease. And I think - after a long - many years, it was sold freehold.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid8480765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11556911\charrsid8926906 Do you remember feeling that your parents had to struggle to make ends meet?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid675531 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11556911\charrsid8926906 No, I don't think we did. No, I think we got on fairly well that way.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid8480765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11556911\charrsid8926906 What difference did it make to the family when father was ill or out of work?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid675531 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11556911\charrsid8926906 Well -
 I don't think he suffered a lot really, not - for one thing he - he had a - group at the Co-op and something but then - he never had - never - never laid up with illness and none of that, he simply carried on almost to the finish.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid8480765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11556911\charrsid8926906 Did it mean the rest of the family had to undertake more duties?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid675531 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11556911\charrsid8926906 
No, I - I don't think - my father right up to the finish was almost active, and I don't think the family had to struggle at all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid8480765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11556911\charrsid8926906 Do you remember anyone having to go to the Guardians or the Parish or 
any charity?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid675531 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11556911\charrsid8926906 
No, not in our family, there were many cases we heard of where they had to - have assistance from the Poor Law they called in then, of course there was no - nothing like it is today, but - we weren't in that distress. But now - we heard of many that were.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid8480765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11556911\charrsid8926906 
When there was someone in the district whom the people disapproved of strongly was there any special way in which they showed it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid675531 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11556911\charrsid8926906 Well I don't know I'm sure.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid8480765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11556911\charrsid8926906 Do you remember anyone being made to leave by rough music or b
eing drummed out?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid675531 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11556911\charrsid8926906 No I don't remember that. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid8480765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11556911\charrsid8926906 
We did say that you father was thirty-three when you were born, that was a mistake wasn't it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid675531 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11556911\charrsid8926906 Yes, it was a mistake.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid8480765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11556911\charrsid8926906 How old was he?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid675531 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11556911\charrsid8926906 He was - forty odd I think.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid8480765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11556911\charrsid8926906 Forty-three would it be?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid675531 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11556911\charrsid8926906 Yes, well I think it was forty-three.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid8480765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11556911\charrsid8926906 Were you given lessons by one of your parents, a tutor or a governess?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid675531 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11556911\charrsid8926906 
No, I - I think we did get a bit of tuition before we went and also the - the other - members of the family would help us that way.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid8480765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11556911\charrsid8926906 Your sister and brother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid675531 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11556911\charrsid8926906 Yes, oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid8480765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11556911\charrsid8926906 That would be at home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid675531 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11556911\charrsid8926906 
Yes. Oh I remember going to - I think I - went to a - as a tiny boy to a - went to North Roskear - what's the name, the - the - Roskear - chapel out there - I d
on't know the name now, anyhow, I think we had that schoolroom while the Basset Road school was being built, 'cos I remember going up to Basset Road, little while afterwards, I think that was - yes, I can remember - yes, I went to the Basset Road school w
hen it was re-opened, 1895 I think, I think I was about five years old then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid8480765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11556911\charrsid8926906 Before that you went to Roskear?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid675531 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11556911\charrsid8926906 No - the - the chapel out here, at - {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}
North Roskear{\*\xmlclose} way. I think they had a schoolroom there while the - school was being built.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid8480765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11556911\charrsid8926906 How old were you when you first went to school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid675531 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11556911\charrsid8926906 
I think I was - well - of course some used to start four years old, some five, I - I can't say exactly my age but - there was no - there was no compulsion I think then when you - you had - I think you had 
to start five but then you could go before that if you wished. That's providing the teachers will allow you of course.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid8480765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11556911\charrsid8926906 Do you Remember Basset Road school being opened?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid675531 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11556911\charrsid8926906 No, I - I don't remember it being opened.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid8480765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11556911\charrsid8926906 When you first started what t
ime of the morning did you go and what time did you come back?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid675531 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11556911\charrsid8926906 
The school then used to - start at nine, nine 'til twelve. And then I think again at - about two 'til four thirty.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid8480765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11556911\charrsid8926906 What kind of school was it? Board school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid675531 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11556911\charrsid8926906 Yes, a board school
. There - there were - boys and girls. The boys were on the top floor and the girls underneath.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid8480765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11556911\charrsid8926906 And infants?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid675531 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11556911\charrsid8926906 And the infants, underneath, yes. On the ground floor.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid8480765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11556911\charrsid8926906 That was a day school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid675531 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11556911\charrsid8926906 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid8480765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11556911\charrsid8926906 How did you get to school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid675531 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11556911\charrsid8926906 Oh we used to walk to school. Never had far to go.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid8480765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11556911\charrsid8926906 About five minutes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid675531 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11556911\charrsid8926906 Yes, about five minutes I should say.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid8480765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11556911\charrsid8926906 Did anyone take you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid675531 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11556911\charrsid8926906 
Well I don't remember being taken, but - I daresay I went with my sister very likely or brother. Very likely the brother I should think.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid8480765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11556911\charrsid8926906 Did you come home to lunch?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid675531 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11556911\charrsid8926906 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid8480765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11556911\charrsid8926906 What did you think of school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid675531 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11556911\charrsid8926906 
Well I was not very fond of school. I think my brother was the most educated of the family. Oh well - for the boys, cos he done a lot of readi
ng. He was always reading, and I remember - going to the - the library for him, while he was having his meals he always had a book up in front of him, and I remember going over the library and picking out a book for him. He was always reading. And I think
 that's a tribute to his education.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid8480765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11556911\charrsid8926906 What school did he go to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid675531 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11556911\charrsid8926906 
He went to the - Basset, no, I - I'm not quite sure. No, I'm not quite sure what school he went.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid8480765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11556911\charrsid8926906 He was ten years older than you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid675531 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11556911\charrsid8926906 Yes. Of course it wouldn't be Basset Road then would it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid8480765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11556911\charrsid8926906 And you disliked school rather? How did you feel about the teachers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid675531 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11556911\charrsid8926906 
Well - on the whole they were very good, I've had a few - smacks on the hands and so on with the cane but - on the whole I think they were very good and they done their best to - to bring us on.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid8480765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11556911\charrsid8926906 Did the teachers emphasise certain things as important in life?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid675531 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11556911\charrsid8926906 Well - I don't know that exactly, I suppose they did you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid8480765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11556911\charrsid8926906 Punctuality?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid675531 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11556911\charrsid8926906 Yes, they were very strict on - on time, being punctual, tho
ugh I was a bit late very often for the school in the mornings.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid8480765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11556911\charrsid8926906 Because of the newspapers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid675531 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11556911\charrsid8926906 It may have been that, but -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid8480765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11556911\charrsid8926906 Did they emphasise particular ways of speaking?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid675531 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11556911\charrsid8926906 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid8480765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11556911\charrsid8926906 Tidiness?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid675531 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11556911\charrsid8926906 No, not overcrowded in the schools then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid8480765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11556911\charrsid8926906 Did the teachers emphasise good manners?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid675531 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11556911\charrsid8926906 
Oh yes, they were very good on that I think, they - they brought the children up very - very properly that way.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid8480765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11556911\charrsid8926906 What about tidiness?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid675531 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11556911\charrsid8926906 Well - I think children on the whole were very tidy the
m days. Though we didn't have a lot of clothes to - to - to put on, we - we always kept clean.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid8480765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11556911\charrsid8926906 
Your brother's reading, was there any special subject do you remember that he had books about?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid675531 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11556911\charrsid8926906 No, I can't remember that but - I know he was very fond
 on the - Conan Doyle's books, I - remember going to the library for them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid8480765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11556911\charrsid8926906 
If you did something at school that the teachers disapproved of what would happen?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid675531 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11556911\charrsid8926906 
Well sometimes you were kept in - in late after school, to do - sort of - punishment a number of words or something like that you know. That's the only - most - most of the punishment we got I think was being kept in a bit late.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid8480765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11556911\charrsid8926906 Were the girls punished the same as the boys?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid675531 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11556911\charrsid8926906 I expect so, I don't - I can't remember that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid8480765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11556911\charrsid8926906 What s
ort of offences would be thought were worthy of punishment? What would you have done for that, to be kept in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid675531 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11556911\charrsid8926906 
Well you - you may have been disobeying their - their teaching like, may have been talking or something like this you know. Nothing very serious.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid8480765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11556911\charrsid8926906 Did your parents show any interest in your school work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid675531 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11556911\charrsid8926906 Oh yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid8480765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11556911\charrsid8926906 Did they ask what you did at school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid675531 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11556911\charrsid8926906 Yes, they were very - keen to know how we got on.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid8480765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11556911\charrsid8926906 Did they ever visit the school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid675531 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11556911\charrsid8926906 I can't remember them going t
o the school, they may have done, but I can't remember. I don't think the parents used to attend the schools - in them days like they do today.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid8480765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11556911\charrsid8926906 Did they meet the teachers at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid675531 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11556911\charrsid8926906 Well - I - I don't remember 'em - meeting the teachers. Though I t
hink - my brother, eldest brother, he was very friendly with one of the teachers, they used to converse a lot I think, and in fact one of our teachers was the - }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13585395\charrsid8926906 interlope}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11556911\charrsid8926906  in the minstrel show we used to put on every year. Mr Quietrell, he was the - the cen
tre man in the minstrel troupe.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid8480765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11556911\charrsid8926906 Put on by whom?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid675531 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11556911\charrsid8926906 
All local people you know, and - I remember this was annual event and I - in one of those - minstrel shows I done my first appearance, I think I was about - about ten years old. No - no, I may hav
e been a little older. Anyhow I remember going on as Malandie the Midget Comedian, but this was a - we had a lovely minstrel show. And then there was a - a private school over here at Roskear used to - he was - the - choirmaster down the Camborne church, 
he had a lot of boys there, were lovely singers. I remember that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid8480765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11556911\charrsid8926906 
Would your parents have chatted with the teachers in the shop or if they met them in the street?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid675531 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11556911\charrsid8926906 Oh I don't remember 'em coming in the shop.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid8480765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11556911\charrsid8926906 Did the other children come from similar types of home to your own?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid675531 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11556911\charrsid8926906 
Well there may have been a few - children locally, but I don't remember very much. We met mostly at school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid8480765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11556911\charrsid8926906 
Did the teachers single out some children for different treatment from the others?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid675531 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11556911\charrsid8926906 Well I - I thi
nk there's a little bit that way. I think they - the master we had, I think he - he paid a little more attention to the higher class boys in business I suppose.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid8480765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11556911\charrsid8926906 Were there any gangs or groups in the school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid675531 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11556911\charrsid8926906 No, no, it - of course there was a - l
ittle clique that used to put we boys up to fight. I - I remember - most every day I had a go at one of the boys there. I was fighting my best friend as a rule. Of course I had - I had proper ginger hair, they thought I had to fight.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid8480765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11556911\charrsid8926906 Were there any children who were left out of things at school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid675531 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11556911\charrsid8926906 Any children left out?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid8480765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11556911\charrsid8926906 Left out of things in play or in school society?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid675531 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11556911\charrsid8926906 Oh no, I don't think there's any distinction that way.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid8480765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11556911\charrsid8926906 Do you remember ever any children coming to school without shoes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid675531 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11556911\charrsid8926906 
No, I don't remember - any children that way. Everybody seemed to be - clothed - perhaps not - sort of efficient as others but the - I don't remember any - anybody coming without shoes, none of that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid8480765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11556911\charrsid8926906 How old were you when you left school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid675531 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11556911\charrsid8926906 Fourteen.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid8480765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11556911\charrsid8926906 Did you go on to any other school afterwards?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid675531 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11556911\charrsid8926906 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid8480765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11556911\charrsid8926906 Would you have stayed longer at school if you had had the opportunity?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid675531 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11556911\charrsid8926906 
No, I - no opportunity in them days. When you finish at fourteen you - it was all over.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid8480765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11556911\charrsid8926906 Did you attend any part time education afterwards, evening classes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid675531 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11556911\charrsid8926906 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid8480765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11556911\charrsid8926906 Do you have any regrets about your education?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid675531 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11556911\charrsid8926906 No, I don't think so.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid8480765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11556911\charrsid8926906 Do you think you benefitted from attending school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid675531 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11556911\charrsid8926906 Oh yes, I think so.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid8480765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11556911\charrsid8926906 While you were at school you did have the part time job of delivering papers?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid675531 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11556911\charrsid8926906 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid8480765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11556911\charrsid8926906 How did you get this job?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid675531 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11556911\charrsid8926906 
Well I don't remember how I got the job, I may have got it from one of the other boys. There was another boy there, he'd left school, and star
ted on this here paper round - and I may have got the job through him. But nothing to do with - with me mother, she didn't make no application that way, it was done all - mostly on me own. It was a voluntary job I took on.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid8480765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11556911\charrsid8926906 What exactly did you have to do in this job?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid675531 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11556911\charrsid8926906 
Well, first of all I had to meet the - early train, quarter to seven - and then I'd do me paper round delivering papers - different parts of the town. And one - one part of the town I had to go right to the top of Beacon Hill, and t
hem long gardens. The - with the Mirror - the - the Morning News and Mercury, the two papers them days, daily papers. And Basset Street, Basset Road, that was all in it, well it was - well I suppose - well after eight when I finished, and must have been -
 not much time to just have a little bit of a meal of some sort then off to school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid8480765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11556911\charrsid8926906 Any of this on Sundays?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid675531 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11556911\charrsid8926906 No. No. But -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid8480765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11556911\charrsid8926906 Saturday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid675531 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11556911\charrsid8926906 
Saturdays yes. But I remember the - the Sunday papers I think was - the People, I'm not sure, was the S
unday paper. That was a penny them days. And - I know - we had a - a chick with three legs, and - Samey Whear said, if you let me have that chick to put on show I'll give you the Sunday paper - for several weeks. Well we had it for two or three weeks and 
then it finished.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid8480765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11556911\charrsid8926906 Saturdays, did you work all day or just the same hours as weekdays?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid675531 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11556911\charrsid8926906 
Same - from - pretty much the same. There was the paper round in the mornings, then - taking out different articles from the paper shop in the midday. Then back
 to school. From school to the shop, see if there's any papers to go out. And then - to meet the next train for the evening papers. Six thirty. That was the Evening Herald, then nine o'clock was a later edition.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid8480765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11556911\charrsid8926906 Did you do any other part time jobs before you left school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid675531 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11556911\charrsid8926906 No. No other jobs.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid8480765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11556911\charrsid8926906 
Did you feel that, I think you said five shillings a week for the newspaper job, was a fair wage or not?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid675531 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11556911\charrsid8926906 Oh yes, that was very good wage really - very useful to my mother that was.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid8480765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11556911\charrsid8926906 You gave it all to mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid675531 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11556911\charrsid8926906 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid8480765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11556911\charrsid8926906 How did you get on with the people who employed you for that work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid675531 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11556911\charrsid8926906 
Oh they were very good, Mr Rowe was the - owner of the paper shop that time. They - they were very nice people.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid8480765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11556911\charrsid8926906 What was your first full time job after leaving school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid675531 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11556911\charrsid8926906 
Well after leaving school - I went apprenticeship to the plumbing trade. I was supposed to serve six years. Shilling a week for the first year, and - shilling rise each year. Well the sixth year you only get six shilling. But I r
emember - being up the street this dinner time and a commercial traveller came on, and - any of you boys want a job? Said, yes, I will. I took his two bags and went around a few shops in Camborne, Stationery shops, then he went to the hotel to have his lu
n
ch, he says, I'll see you after lunch and - take my bags up the station. I think I had a half a crown for that. I should only have got about a - couple of bob in the - all the week in the job, and I met the boss on the way. He near - nearly fell to the gr
ound when he saw me carrying these bags. You see, casual labourers got more than people that were serving their apprenticeship.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid8480765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11556911\charrsid8926906 How did you get your apprenticeship job?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid675531 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11556911\charrsid8926906 Well I - I'm not sure, maybe have been an advert for apprentices, but - it di
dn't turn out - very beneficial as a plumber 'cos they done most of the work then - delivering these here - making these here - and delivering these here tin cases for the safety fuse at Tuckingmill. But as a plumber from Truro that came on with us and I 
-
 eventually I left him and went with him before my apprenticeship was up and - I - I soon got on and learnt the trade well, he was - one of the finest plumbers I remember being in contact with. We got on very well indeed. I - turned out I suppose a pretty
 good plumber, at least so they say.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid8480765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11556911\charrsid8926906 You didn't have to sign any articles with this first employer?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid675531 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11556911\charrsid8926906 No. I don't think so.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid8480765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11556911\charrsid8926906 The safety fuse, this was just after the end of the Boer War wasn't it?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid675531 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11556911\charrsid8926906 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid8480765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11556911\charrsid8926906 Safety fuse was expanding for Africa then wasn't it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid675531 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11556911\charrsid8926906 
Yes. Yes. Yes, I sold papers - during the Boer War, remember being on the platform at Camborne when - lot of the miners were coming back from South Africa. Of course they - the said, if the Boers win, we finish in Africa. Of cou
rse I think them days they used to go - in charge of these here natives out there and get good money.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid8480765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11556911\charrsid8926906 Do you remember miners leaving Camborne for South Africa in those days?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid675531 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11556911\charrsid8926906 Oh yes - I think the - a lot of these - I think they used to get money 
lent to them, for their passage. I remember 'em going up the station with the old - old landau they used to call them, the old cab, open cab and waving their hands going up the station, going off to Africa. I remember that as a boy.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid8480765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11556911\charrsid8926906 Do you remember any of them coming back?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid675531 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11556911\charrsid8926906 Yes. Oh yes. Lot of 'em come back to die really.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid8480765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11556911\charrsid8926906 Coming back at Camborne Station?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid675531 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11556911\charrsid8926906 Yes, this 'ere - miners complaint. Silicosis do they call it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid8480765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11556911\charrsid8926906 Remember any of them coming back rich?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid675531 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11556911\charrsid8926906 Oh yes. YES? THEY cam
e back with a lot of money. But they soon spent it, they - spent mostly in the - in the pubs and so on and treating other people. They always come back and buy a pony and - and a jingle, I remember one fellow, he bought a pony and jingle and - he got it f
rom some other fellow that - that been - visiting the pubs I suppose and - every time he got to a pub the old pony would pull in there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid8480765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11556911\charrsid8926906 This first employment, how long actually were you with that employer?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid675531 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11556911\charrsid8926906 What, this second employer?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid8480765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11556911\charrsid8926906 The first one.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid675531 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11556911\charrsid8926906 Oh - oh I - I think I was with him about two or three years I think.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid8480765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11556911\charrsid8926906 And then to the one at {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}
{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname City}}Truro{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid675531 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11556911\charrsid8926906 
Yes, he - he - he left that employment, and started on his own in Camborne. He had all the run of the town.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid8480765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11556911\charrsid8926906 This was your second employer you mean?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid675531 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11556911\charrsid8926906 
Second employer. Yes. Yes, he worked on them houses up at - other end of - Mount Pleasant Road there, the name was - Mr Lee built them houses, he done all the work up there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid8480765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11556911\charrsid8926906 What exactly did you have to do in this job?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid675531 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11556911\charrsid8926906 
Well - we done all the heating - hot water system which was - done with a Cronish range you see during them days, and - all the lead work on the roof - he put me up and - and got me to do the work the same as himself, and eventually I got well along the j
ob. I remember - he - oh it's - somebody called Mr Old, they had a - built a house down at Mount Pleasant Road, but it started falling down as he was building it. He had somebody there that - didn't understand the job much. And we was up on - on 
{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname address}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname Street}}Cadogan Road{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}
 on these houses and saw - Mr Old running up the - the road. He said, come down, come down at once, we're flooded out. We went down, there was the water running out the door, he never turned the water off, and - then he said, you'd better put this job ri
ght for me plumber, he said, it - it's been a failure since we had it. So - anyhow he said, how do you - how do you work - hour - hour work or day work? You can have hour work if you like Mr Old. Well it's work. Well - now, all he said well - wasn't a lot
 
of fittings in the town, you'd better go off on the bicycle and get the fittings. Now - hurry up, he said, you know this is day work. Well when I got outside the gate - gate he said, take your time, go for a ride somewhere. Well when I was coming back I m
e
t Mr Old and my boss - where have you been all this time? Well I couldn't get those fittings. Oh well, I'll have to go myself. Well then off he went. Of course the pubs were open all day in them days and - anyhow - when done the job we couldn't get the mo
n
ey. Well then - he said to me one day, you go up and get that money out of Mr Olds, up to Beadon. He kept a stuffed bird shop. And we went up there, he said, you guard the door, and get the money before I go up. He wanted - wanted us to have a stuffed bir
d. So we - my - my boss, said, no, that's no good to us for Sunday dinner. Anyhow we got the money eventually.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid8480765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11556911\charrsid8926906 Were people paid in kind sometimes in those days?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid675531 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11556911\charrsid8926906 No, I don't think so, no. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid8480765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11556911\charrsid8926906 Like farmers sometimes would like to pay you by giving you a side of beef.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid675531 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11556911\charrsid8926906 
Yes, farmers - oh - oh yes, they done that in the farming business, but not in our line.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid8480765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11556911\charrsid8926906 What hours did you work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid675531 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11556911\charrsid8926906 
Well - we start about - I think it was seven - half past seven in the mornings 'til five or half pa
st five in the evenings, but Holmans, they used to start half past six of a morning, stop half hour for breakfast, and then they'd work on 'til half past five in the evening. And also Saturday work - all Saturday morning 'til - I think it was one o'clock.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid8480765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11556911\charrsid8926906 Did you work Saturdays?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid675531 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11556911\charrsid8926906 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid8480765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11556911\charrsid8926906 Did you have any half days?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid675531 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11556911\charrsid8926906 No. Only - only - the Saturday afternoon.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid8480765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11556911\charrsid8926906 Any Sunday work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid675531 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11556911\charrsid8926906 No Sunday work.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid8480765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11556911\charrsid8926906 Did you have any holidays with pay?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid675531 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11556911\charrsid8926906 No. No holidays with pay and we - also w
e didn't get paid for Bank Holidays in them days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid8480765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11556911\charrsid8926906 Do you remember your first pay, how much you were paid?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid675531 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11556911\charrsid8926906 
No, I don't remember - the first amount, whether I had nine - no, I done very well off the - second employer.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid8480765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11556911\charrsid8926906 You felt it was a fair wage?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid675531 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11556911\charrsid8926906 Oh yes. OH yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid8480765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11556911\charrsid8926906 Did you give any of the money to your mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid675531 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11556911\charrsid8926906 
Oh yes. Yes, I was quite proud to bring home the paypacket to my mother. But she never kept me short of pocket money.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid8480765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11556911\charrsid8926906 You'd give her the packet and she would pay you pocket money?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid675531 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11556911\charrsid8926906 That's right. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid8480765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11556911\charrsid8926906 How did you get on with the other people you worked with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid675531 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11556911\charrsid8926906 Oh got along very well really.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid8480765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11556911\charrsid8926906 How did your employer treat you, starting with the first one?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid675531 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11556911\charrsid8926906 Well - the - the first one you see - we - we 
done mostly tin plate work, well that - wasn't much good, not - he said we - we were going to learn all the - plumbing business but we - we - we couldn't - we couldn't learn on this job, not the plumbing business.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid8480765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11556911\charrsid8926906 How did you feel about him?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid675531 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11556911\charrsid8926906 Well - I wasn't very well satisfied there in that job.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid8480765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11556911\charrsid8926906 Nor about the work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid675531 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11556911\charrsid8926906 No.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid8480765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11556911\charrsid8926906 As work did you like it or dislike it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid675531 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11556911\charrsid8926906 Well I - I got to like the plumbing job eventually.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid8480765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11556911\charrsid8926906 Your second employer, how did you get on with that firm?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid675531 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11556911\charrsid8926906 
Oh I got on very well with them until - the finish, and then - well, he'd gone in a bit ridiculous in the town I think, he owed a lot of money different towns - different shops and that, and - he - he never paid me when it come the Saturday, first - firs
t Saturday so I - anyhow - second Saturday he said, I haven't got the money, he said, not from the employer, 'cos he used to do a lot of - of work supplying the labour and the employer supplied the material. Well then, eventually I got three weeks without
 
any money. But - anyhow - I - I said, if you don't pay me, I said, I'm going to put you in the County Court. Well, I went to - I went in to Redruth to work, a firm in there - we had a job down at Porthleven, I went down there and I saw all these here ligh
t
s in the - round the harbour, so I said to - somebody there, I said, what's all these lights? Well they said, they're - trying to light up the harbour with acetylene lamps. Well I went in the hotel, the Commercial it was there to have a drink and - there 
w
as my previous employer there with this here other fellow. So he said, what are you going to have to drink? I said, I don't want that, I want that money. So - anyhow it appears he got hold of a fellow with a bit of money and they were trying out this here
 acetylene plant for lighting up the harbour. There were no lights in the harbour in them days. But I don't know - I think it fell through.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid8480765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11556911\charrsid8926906 Did you get your money?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid675531 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11556911\charrsid8926906 
I got my money eventually. I - I put him in the County Court, and when I was sitti
ng down waiting for the judge, I think it went up in front of the - the Clerk of the Court, and then - door opened and he called me out. - So - I went out and he said, do you mind if I pay downstairs. I said, don't mind Sam as long as I get the money. We 
w
ent downstairs to square things up, I think he dodged all expenses that way, and we went then and had a drink and - part - parted the best of pals. The last time I saw him was - when I was going up in the Army, 1914, I saw him at Chacewater Station, and -
 Sam said, I've got the very job for you. I got plenty of work out at - out at - Newquay way. And Perranporth. I said, too late Sam, I'm in the Army now.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid8480765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11556911\charrsid8926906 
So how long actually were you with the second employer, you learned most of your plumbing with him? You left him then just before the first world war did you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid675531 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11556911\charrsid8926906 Yes, yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid8480765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11556911\charrsid8926906 
Did you go on to another employment before the Army, between him and the Army?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid675531 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11556911\charrsid8926906 Yes,. I was in Redruth. The job in there.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid8480765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11556911\charrsid8926906 That was plumbing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid675531 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11556911\charrsid8926906 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid8480765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11556911\charrsid8926906 Until the war?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid675531 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11556911\charrsid8926906 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid8480765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11556911\charrsid8926906 So in 1914 you joined the Army, did you serve throughout the war?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid675531 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11556911\charrsid8926906 
Yes, and - I - I went to India, we relieved the - I - in the second Fort Battalion, the Cornwalls, we went to India to relieve the regular Army out there,
 and then 1917 they wanted a - fifty volunteers for unknown destination and I - volunteered for that and - I finished up in Mesopotamia. That was the end of the war then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid8480765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11556911\charrsid8926906 You came back to Camborne in 1918, what was your first job after that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid675531 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11556911\charrsid8926906 Wel
l, my first job was - traveling with a theatrical company. This Inez Howard's - dramatic company. I - I went - went and toured with them. We were - went different parts of the country, we opened at - {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}
Weston-Super-Mare{\*\xmlclose} I think it was. We toured right up to the {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}Midlands{\*\xmlclose}
. Well then I had a letter from my sister in Nanpean asking if I'd come back and - take charge of a - charabanc business. Well when I got down there things were not so rosy, my brother-in-law was all right but the sister wanted to know if I'd g
ot any money to put in the business. I said, no. Well then I left that. Well then I went - in - in concert parties round the - Cornwall.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid8480765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11556911\charrsid8926906 
How long were you with the touring party before you came back to Nanpean roughly?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid675531 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11556911\charrsid8926906 Well I should say about six months.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid8480765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11556911\charrsid8926906 And then to another touring company?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid675531 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11556911\charrsid8926906 
Well - well we ran our own - theatrical business after that, we had our own theatre, wooden theatre.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid8480765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11556911\charrsid8926906 Transportable?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid675531 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11556911\charrsid8926906 Yes. Portable theatre.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid8480765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11556911\charrsid8926906 How long were you employed in that work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid675531 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11556911\charrsid8926906 Well I couldn't say exactly, I should say about - two years.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid8480765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11556911\charrsid8926906 You toured Cornwall, did you tour outside of Cornwall?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid675531 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11556911\charrsid8926906 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid8480765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11556911\charrsid8926906 Just toured Cornwall?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid675531 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11556911\charrsid8926906 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid8480765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11556911\charrsid8926906 What happened then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid675531 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11556911\charrsid8926906 Well the - they sold that business to another p
arty, sold that wooden theatre. That went up to - Poole in Dorset I think that theatre did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid8480765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11556911\charrsid8926906 
What part in the company did you have, were you employed by or a partner in it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid675531 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11556911\charrsid8926906 Yes, I - I was a partner there, and - I - had to do mostly small parts, b
ut - I also had to take the money at the pay box. Well I'd go on and get murdered and then come back and take some more money. I remember being - murdered three times one night. And the people - my brother said, they want more blood. I said, can't have an
ymore blood out of me.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid8480765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11556911\charrsid8926906 Can you remember any of the plays?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid675531 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11556911\charrsid8926906 
Oh yes. Yes, oh yes, the - a number of Sweeney Todd mostly. I know - I played a foreign seaman there at the back of the Plume of Feathers Hotel at Pool. Anyhow - Sweeny, instead of polishi
ng me off - his accomplice, she fell in love with me a bit I think and - I was put down in the cellar, punishment, no food or water. I was chained up, roped up and so on and put down through the trap door. Then I - After I unroped myself a bit and went up
 
to Charlie Tucker's at the back of the pub and had a pint of beer, I could listen to the programme from there from the bar, and - I had a pint and I believe I was in me second pint when they said - the cue was coming near for me to get back on the stage a
g
ain. So I rushed down, got underneath the - the stage and undone - roped myself up again, put a bit of white stuff all over my face and a bit in my hair, then I rushed up, pushed up from under the trap door and - the - woman that used to make the - the pi
es out of the dead bodies they said she - splashed water round me and I said, oh give me water, give me water. And the people in the audience said, poor fellow, been under the stage, nothing to drink for all these house, and I'd just had nearly two pints.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid8480765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11556911\charrsid8926906 This was in the open air was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid675531 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11556911\charrsid8926906 
No, we had a wood theatre. Made of matchboard and that, because I remember my brother came around, I - I'd been on and got murdered, had come on and take more money and he - he said - got any struts with you? I sa
id, what is it? Oh the - the theatre'll be down in a minute or two, we had to go round and - and strut up the side, the house - we was all packed out and people leaning against the patch wood side, and we had to go and strut the theatre up to keep 'em fal
ling down.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid8480765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11556911\charrsid8926906 
Where did you usually put the theatre up, any sort of open space like the pub yard?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid675531 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11556911\charrsid8926906 
Yes. But when we went to Perranporth and there was a lot of waste land there. So we pitched our theatre there, and the grocer come out. Oh we applied 
I believe to - the Lord of the Manor or Lord of this here land in Truro, or the solicitor, and he said, you can build your theatre down on that there mine land. Well we went down there and built the theatre, or started building up and - the grocer's wife 
came out, said, what are you doing here? We're putting a theatre up here. OH you've no right here, this is our land. Well there was argument there between the grocer, he'd been to {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname City
}}Truro{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose} market, when he come back and anyhow there was an argument about this h
ere and - we didn't pay anybody. He claimed it and the - and the mining people claimed it, so we got away without paying any rent at all there. Perranporth.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid8480765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11556911\charrsid8926906 How long did you stay at a time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid675531 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11556911\charrsid8926906 Well you stay until your business go down you see. When
 the business go down well then of course you - you pack up. I remember being there a bank holiday and - we were good way up from the beach, so - most of the people being a fine day were down on the beach, so I had an idea. I suggested that we'd have the 
-
 the back of the theatre free - to people. Well that brought a lot of people up from the beaches, come down here from the Clay district, the - their wagons, used to clean out their clay wagons and drive down from St Austell. Anyhow, we got a crowd up ther
e, outside the theatre - well now I said, standing room only - free. Well then of course you'd get them up into the seats afterwards you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid8480765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11556911\charrsid8926906 Did you make a fair bit of money on that entertainment?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid675531 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11556911\charrsid8926906 Oh yes, we - we done very well, but - I remember
 - the pianist we had, he - he and his wife and a - a little daughter, they used to play parts as well, and - you - you wait until the business go down then of course you go on what they call shares you see, and then eventually you had - to pack up and ge
t
 to somewhere else you see. But I remember - George Valler, the pianist with the portable theatre in Redruth, he - they were doing very poor business eventually and he said, what about going to Helston Flora? Well he had a little yacht piano, a little fiv
e
 octave piano in this caravan and we had a pony and trolley, so - we put the piano on this here trolley and went off to Helston Flora and - we went up to the Hotel there, on the Lizard, going on towards Lizard, and changing the pierrot costumes and starte
d
 busking in the town. And - we done very well. We - we started there the midday dance, we had to stop 'til they went by, then we carried on and - we shared I think about two or three pound there. And little Dolly Crozier, she was a lovely - entertainer, b
u
t she didn't like the idea of being on a wagon singing so she packed up, but she had her share. We - had all this here money to share out and we went to a pub there on the way back and shared out the money. Well they done very well there 'cos - a man and 
wife in a theatre then wouldn't get more than two pound ten, combined salary, man and wife.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid8480765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11556911\charrsid8926906 Would that be for a number of performance or just for the one day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid675531 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11556911\charrsid8926906 No, that was just the one performance you see, you play the drama.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid8480765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11556911\charrsid8926906 Helston Flora?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid675531 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11556911\charrsid8926906 
Yes. East Lynne or Sweeny Todd or - what it was you see. And this is busking now I'm talking about now, and - Helston Flora.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid8480765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11556911\charrsid8926906 Was it always easy to sort out the money between you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid675531 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11556911\charrsid8926906 No, I don't think we - we quarrelled that way.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid8480765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11556911\charrsid8926906 No trouble?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid675531 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11556911\charrsid8926906 
No. I know we - we had one actor, I think he's called Duval - he was a fine actor and he got stranded in Helston with the - with another theatre, and he walked to Camborne, and - but we was at Pool then, and asked for a job, well - my brother sa
id we couldn't employ the both of them, him and his wife, but we'd take him on 'til he got another job, and - he came on as an actor. Well then, he left us without any notice to go to Ireland, he had a job in Ireland, but - when he got there, in Ireland, 
he was knocked down, they thought he was a - somebody come to - to break the strike. And the old chap got killed. Duval - in Ireland.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid8480765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11556911\charrsid8926906 Which brother was this?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid675531 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11556911\charrsid8926906 This is eldest brother.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid8480765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11556911\charrsid8926906 Bill?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid675531 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11556911\charrsid8926906 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid8480765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11556911\charrsid8926906 Would he have been in charge of the troupe?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid675531 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11556911\charrsid8926906 Yes, yes, he was in charge.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid8480765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11556911\charrsid8926906 What particular part did he take in the plays, any or was he just manager?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid675531 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11556911\charrsid8926906 
Oh he was a - a - an actor, he used to play most of the - used to call the villain parts, the heavy parts in the play. He'd play 
the juvenile lead sometimes. Of course I wasn't much of an actor myself, but - I used to do a turn, of course with the portable theatre, when you - when you play your - your drama or whatever it was you had a sort of variety, and each artist come on and s
ing a song or whatever it was and then a little - sketch to finish. 'Course I eventually packed up this here theatrical business and - of course went on a - as a plumber.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid8480765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11556911\charrsid8926906 How long were you doing the theatrical work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid675531 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11556911\charrsid8926906 Oh - several years I suppose,
 I - couldn't say exactly. As for the tour I had under our own theatre.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid8480765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11556911\charrsid8926906 
1926 when the general strike took place were you working as a plumber then or doing the acting work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid675531 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11556911\charrsid8926906 I don't remember that. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid8480765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11556911\charrsid8926906 What year were you married?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid675531 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11556911\charrsid8926906 19 - 26 was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid8480765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11556911\charrsid8926906 
I think Mrs Blewitt said you were married in 1920? So were you doing the plays then or had you returned to plumbing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid675531 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11556911\charrsid8926906 Oh plumbing then. Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid8480765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11556911\charrsid8926906 
So just before then you would return to the occupation of plumbing perhaps would you think, just before you were married?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid675531 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11556911\charrsid8926906 Yes. Yes.
