Well - you see the - the point was - when you got children in rooms you don't feel - satisfied really because - you've got to - to keep the children from moving around like freely, so I said, w
hen - when this job finished I'll go back to Cornwall. And I wrote down to my brother, that's the eldest brother, to look out for a house. Well then - there was two places we could have gone, one was a Gerry in Camborne, of course that had - a rough name 
i
n them days, another was in Lanner. Well, we went down to Lanner. Just after I got down I got a letter from the Secretary of the plumbers union at Colwyn Bay, offering me a - a job - at Colwyn Bay, nine months guaranteed work and the fare back if I cared 
to come back, because I know what you feel like when you get back to your own country, you don't want to move. Well I didn't take that job.
